          "username": "krishnaa96"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-22 10:56:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(2 comments)\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> (10 comments)\n> \n> some suggestions for improvements but my main issue is in a comment below re. the idea that each template is bound to a certain schema_set?! I don't think that is correct, was that discussed with Tony?\n> \n> I did not review the testware until this is clarified...\n\nThe table which we have now in the app will have an entry for a single xpath query. If we look at that way, it will be bound to a single schema set. We could remove it from the id(currently it is a composite key, id + schema-set) and have only id as a primary key, but still, the template will be bound to a single schema set.\n\nWe could handle the multiple queries in a layer on top of this one, may be using a different table",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
